            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

    }

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>

        <td>90</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Natural sound. Birds perched 1-2m above the ground in a privet thicket along the edge of the grounds just behind a mulberry tree with ripe berries. One bird singing initially, but sounded as though a second joined in at times. </p>

<h1>Habitat</h1>

<p>29-acre estate centrally located in Oxford, MS consisting of antebellum home surrounded by lawns and adjacent forest. Privet hedges and small thickets divide the grounds into distinct lawn units. Bordered on all sides by mature oak-hickory forest. Forest edge consists of oak spp, hickory spp, red cedar, mulberry, with understory along the edge dominated by privet (Ligustrum sp.). Grounds around the house include isolated trees and manicured hedges. A path from the end of the parking area leads northward ~1 km through the forest to the northern edge of the property abutting the University of Mississippi campus</p>

<h1>Editing</h1>

<p>Edited in Adobe Audition. Butterworth high-pass filter, order 3, cutoff frequency 2 kHz</p>

<h1>Equipment</h1>

<p>Fostex FR-2 digital recorder with Sennheiser microphone and Telinga pro 22" parabolic reflector.</p>

<p>bird-seen:no</p>

<p>playback-used:no</p>

        <td>United States</td>
        <td>

        <td>90</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Natural sound. Bird calling from within a small patch of forest between a parking area and the grounds. Three individuals present but only one vocalizing.</p>

<h1>Habitat</h1>

<p>29-acre estate centrally located in Oxford, MS consisting of antebellum home surrounded by lawns and adjacent forest. Privet hedges and small thickets divide the grounds into distinct lawn units. Bordered on all sides by mature oak-hickory forest. Forest edge consists of oak spp, hickory spp, red cedar, mulberry, with understory along the edge dominated by privet (Ligustrum sp.). Grounds around the house include isolated trees and manicured hedges. A path from the end of the parking area leads northward ~1 km through the forest to the northern edge of the property abutting the University of Mississippi campus</p>

<h1>Editing</h1>

<p>Edited in Adobe Audition. Butterworth high-pass filter, order 3, cutoff frequency 2 kHz</p>

<h1>Equipment</h1>

<p>Fostex FR-2 digital recorder with Sennheiser microphone and Telinga pro 22" parabolic reflector.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>The best one-stop shopping for song and a great call variety, e.g., three rasp types at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(191063, 129);'>2:09</a>, repeated some later, seemingly as a prelude to a short, soft song, and after those many whit, burr, whit-burr, pink or plink and so forth; mostly one bird, but multiple individuals present and probably involved in the calling at sunset.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>

        <td>700</td>
        <td>alarm/fuss calls, call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>the constant whip and the occasional soft rattle, e.g., at <a onclick='xc.playFrom(190057, 64.9);'>1:04.9</a>, are both from the thrush, which was perhaps alarmed by the hawk (but was not mobbing it directly); other birds, such as the Myrtle Warbler, were also stirred up, but joined the thrush rather than going to the hawk</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>900</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Multiple Swainson's thrushes recorded in boreal forest about 200 m east along the Caps Ridge Trail from the Jefferson Notch parking lot.</p>

Edits to the file: trimmed and normalized to -3 dB.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/cs'>esky</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/da'>Dansk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/de'>Deutsch</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/et'>Eesti</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/en'>English</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/es'>Espaol</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fr'>Franais</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/hu'>Magyar</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/it'>Italiano</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/lt'>Lietuvi</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/nl'>Nederlands</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/no'>Norsk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pl'>Polski</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt'>Portugus</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt_BR'>Portugus do Brasil</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ru'></a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sk'>Slovenina</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fi'>Suomi</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sv'>Svenska</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ja'></a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ko'></a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_CN'></a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_TW'></a></li>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>call, flight call, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Two Swainson's Thrushes countersinging, giving call and flight notes, and one vaguely Grey-cheeked Thrush type note from both birds.  Interesting duet.  Spruce, pine, and birch forest, northwest Ontario.  Birds recorded from a forest road</p>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>One singing individual close to me (5-10 meters away) with one or two others in the background. Habitat: short, mixed deciduous trees and berry bushes (blackberry, thimbleberry, salmonberry) on a hill above a steep stream. Bird not seen, but sounded to be singing about 1-3 meters up one of the deciduous trees. It was starting to get very dark at this point. Weather: a few high clouds, still relatively warm temperatures, no breeze.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>
        0:44
        </td>
        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/DUOIJSQTJC'>Laura Shields</a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2014-07-21</td>
        <td> 16:30</td>
      
        <td>United States</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=43.7597&long=-110.7423&loc=Grand+Teton+National+Park+%28near++Alta%29%2C+Teton+County%2C+Wyoming">Grand Teton National Park (near  Alta), Teton County, Wyoming</a>
        </td>
        <td>2068</td>
        <td>call, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>These birds (Swainson's Thrushes I think), were heard along the trail to Inspiration Point at Jenny Lake in Grand Teton NP. The birds were calling to each other from lower branches of various trees that were right along the path at the edge of the water (there is a lot of water sound in the audio recording). The birds were originally heard when the sun was out and weather was nice, but the recording was made just before a rain/hail storm hit the area.</p>

<p>I cut together two parts of recordings here  the first 7 seconds includes only bird calls, and the remainder of the recording is an unmodified mixture of calls and songs. Apologies that there is also a little bit of noise from people talking and moving around. I do have longer recordings, but they include even more people noise.</p>

<p><a href="https://www.dropbox.com/sc/st9wc1hnq65ugtu/AACsOAfKX9FjesojyoBe7ASda">Here</a> is a Dropbox link with photos. The first photo is of my two friends searching for the birds, which shows how close to the edge of Jenny Lake we were. The second photo has a red circle around one of the birds in question, and the last photo is the full uncropped unmarked version of the second photo (mystery bird is just right of center).</p>

<p>bird-seen:yes</p>
<p>   </p></div><a class='fancybox' rel='sono' href='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/DUOIJSQTJC/ffts/XC195779-large.png' title='XC195779: Swainson&#039;s Thrush (Catharus ustulatus) by Laura Shields'>[sono]</a></div></td>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

            <li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/cs'>esky</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/da'>Dansk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/de'>Deutsch</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/et'>Eesti</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/en'>English</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/es'>Espaol</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fr'>Franais</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/hu'>Magyar</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/it'>Italiano</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/lt'>Lietuvi</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/nl'>Nederlands</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/no'>Norsk</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pl'>Polski</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt'>Portugus</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/pt_BR'>Portugus do Brasil</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ru'></a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sk'>Slovenina</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/fi'>Suomi</a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/sv'>Svenska</a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ja'></a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/ko'></a></li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_CN'></a>*</li><li ><a rel='nofollow' href='/lang/zh_TW'></a></li>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

        <td>
        <span class='common-name'><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus'>Swainson's Thrush</a></span> (<span class='scientific-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span>)

        <td>
        0:50
        </td>
        <td>
        <a href='/contributor/UQLLTZLENZ'>KevinHHood</a>
        </td>
        
        <td>2013-05-22</td>
        <td> 13:04</td>
      
        <td>Canada</td>
        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=49.2895&long=-122.7951&loc=Coquitlam%2C+Greater+Vancouver%2C+British+Columbia">Coquitlam, Greater Vancouver, British Columbia</a>
        </td>
        <td>40</td>
        <td>song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Habitat was mixed forest riparian.  The bird was seen briefly and changed position every few minutes but generally stayed within 2 to 4 meters of the ground (well below canopy).  Weather was warm, little wind, partially overcast.  Roughly 1 to 4 seconds after each song a short single chirp response was heard from, I believe, a different bird some distance away.  I have been hearing what I believe are Swainson's Thrush calls for several days but today was the first time that I heard their song.</p>

<p>Recording is unedited (some clicks between songs were removed without changing intervals).</p>

<p>Recorded using an Olympus VN-702PC recorder and a Sennheiser MKE 400 microphone.</p>

{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>

                <h4>Subspecies</h4>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

            <li><a href="?pg=12&view=1">concise</a></li>

            </div>
            </p>

        <td>50</td>
        <td>, begging call, begging/copulatory, call, female, male, song </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Four to 5 birds within relatively small area. Song playback very briefly used, answered immediately by several calling birds. Two males observed in chase, then brief copulation observed between 1 of the males and female- this occurring sometime between 8.5 and 18 seconds of this recording- in small sparsely-branched red cedar in tiny opening surrounded by dense rough-leaf dogwood and box-elder maple- approximately 20' above ground. Spring migrants. Semi-mature/late succession/riparian.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>

            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/b-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22incanus%22'>incanus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Godfrey, 1952)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/c-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22oedicus%22'>oedicus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Oberholser, 1899)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/d-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22olive-backed+subspecies+group%2C+presumably+swainsoni%22'>olive-backed subspecies group, presumably swainsoni</a></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/e-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22swainsoni%22'>swainsoni</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Tschudi, 1845)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/a-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22ustulatus%22'>ustulatus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/g-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22ustulatus+group%22'>ustulatus group</a></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>two types of call, switching after <a onclick='xc.playFrom(188834, 67);'>1:07</a>; some good, loud calls, but messy with water and other birds</p>

{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            
            <table id='map-table'>
            <tr>
            <td id='map-cell'>
            <div id='map-canvas'></div>
            </td>
            <td>
            <div class='map-sidebar'>
            
            <h3>Map Legend</h3>
        
            <div class="map-legend">
                <h4>Subspecies</h4>
                <ul><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/b-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22incanus%22'>incanus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Godfrey, 1952)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/c-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22oedicus%22'>oedicus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Oberholser, 1899)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/d-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22olive-backed+subspecies+group%2C+presumably+swainsoni%22'>olive-backed subspecies group, presumably swainsoni</a></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/e-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22swainsoni%22'>swainsoni</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Tschudi, 1845)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/a-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22ustulatus%22'>ustulatus</a> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></span></li><li><span class="marker-image"><img class="icon" src="/static/img/markers/g-14.png" /></span> <span class="marker-text"><a href='/species/Catharus-ustulatus?query=ssp:%22ustulatus+group%22'>ustulatus group</a></span></li></ul><h4>Unclassified</h4>

        <td>
          <a href="/location/map?lat=34.1849&long=-118.1223&loc=Country+Club+Drive%2C+Altadena%2C+Los+Angeles+County%2C+California">Country Club Drive, Altadena, Los Angeles County, California</a>
        </td>
        <td>380</td>
        <td>flight call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Flight calls of migrating Swainson's thrushes at night.  Three other flight calls that sound different are also audible but I do not know what they are.</p>

<p>I also used a 30x spotting scope and counted 48 birds fly in front of the gibbous Moon shortly after I obtained the recording.  During that interval, I heard more of the calls on this recording.</p>

<p>Background noise from air conditioners in a nearby building is also audible.  </p>

<p>Recorded with an Olympus LS-10S equipped with a 22 inch Telinga paraboloid and a Sennheiser ME62 microphone aimed at an angle of 45 degrees toward the northeast.  </p>

<p>Modifications to the file: cropped. </p>

<p>bird-seen:no</p>

        <td>812</td>
        <td>call </td>
          
                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>NO AUDIO OR OTHER HARRASSMENT was employed to attract or otherwise change the behavior of these birds.</p>

<p>This is a cool albeit very common call that I transcribe as the "pip-purrrrr." The typical SWTH "pip" call is repeated 1-4 times by itself, interspersed with the immediate, burry but musical "purrrrrrr" call.</p>
<p>   </p></div><a class='fancybox' rel='sono' href='http://www.xeno-canto.org/sounds/uploaded/FOAPDRBSBG/ffts/XC168122-large.png' title='XC168122: Swainson&#039;s Thrush (Catharus ustulatus) by Ken Blankenship'>[sono]</a></div></td>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};


var xcmap = null;
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});

</script>

            <h1>Swainson's Thrush &middot; <span class='sci-name'>Catharus ustulatus</span> &middot; <span class='authority'>(Nuttall, 1840)</span></h1>
            
            <ul class='taxonomy order'>
            <li>Order: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?o=PASSERIFORMES'>PASSERIFORMES</a>
            <ul class='family'>
            <li>Family: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?f=Turdidae'>Turdidae</a> (Thrushes)
            <ul class='genus'>
            <li>Genus: <a href='/explore/taxonomy?g=Catharus'>Catharus</a></li>
            <ul class='species'>
            <li>Species: <span class='sci-name'>ustulatus</span></li>
            </ul>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            </ul>

                <td><div class='remarks readmore'><p>Poor/ noise and somewhat distant. Recorded while standing in several inches of water near edge of shady seasonal pool.  Mature black willow with dense under-story of box-elder maple, others, weeds and vines.</p>

xc.initMap = function()
{
    try {
        var map = xc.createMap("map-canvas", "http://www.xeno-canto.org/ranges/Catharus_ustulatus.kmz?v=2", false);
        map.setMarkers(xc.initialMarkers.markers, xc.initialMarkers.specs, true);

        return map;
    } catch (e) {
        return null;
    }
};

    xcmap = xc.initMap();
});
